@startuml SearchUser

actor Admin
boundary "UserListPage" as View #lightblue
participant ":userRoute" as Route #lightblue
control "authMiddleware" as Auth #Orange
control "userController" as Controller #lightblue
participant ":userService" as Service #lightblue
entity "userModel" as Model #lightblue
database "MongoDB" as MongoDB #yellow

group Search User
note right of Admin: Search by username or email
Admin -> View: 1. Enter keyword (e.g. "john")
activate Admin
activate View

View -> Route: 2. GET /api/users/search?keyword=john
activate Route
Route -> Auth: 3. authenticateUser(req) & authorizeRole()
activate Auth
ref over Auth : 4. 3.0 Verify Token & Check Role

opt Authentication/Authorization Failed
    Auth --> Route: 5.1. Return 401/403 Error
    Route --> View: 5.2. Show error
    View --> Admin: 5.3. Display error message
end
Auth --> Route: 6. User authenticated & authorized
deactivate Auth
Route -> Controller: 7. searchUsers(req, res)
activate Controller

Controller -> Service: 8. searchUsers(keyword)
activate Service

note right of Service: Search by username or email

Service -> Model: 9. findUsers(keyword)
activate Model

Model -> MongoDB: 10. Execute query
activate MongoDB
MongoDB --> Model: 11. Return results
deactivate MongoDB

Model --> Service: 12. Return user list
deactivate Model

alt Users found

    Service --> Controller: 12.1. Return user list
    

    Controller --> Route: 12.1.1. Return user list
    
    Route --> View: 12.1.2. Render user list
    
    
    View --> Admin: 12.1.3. Display result
    
else No users found

    Service --> Controller: 12.2. Return empty list
    deactivate Service

    Controller --> Route: 12.2.1. Return empty list
    deactivate Controller

    Route --> View: 12.2.2. Show "No user found"
    deactivate Route

    View --> Admin: 12.2.3. Display empty state message
    deactivate View
    deactivate Admin
end

end
@enduml
